OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CMonday:FA band of rain, with embedded
OL,6,Fheavier pulses, spreads east during
OL,7,Fthe morning. Brighter conditions
OL,8,Ffollow but scattered, possibly
OL,9,Fthundery showers develop, though these
OL,10,Ftending to ease by late afternoon.
OL,11,
OL,12,COutlook for Tuesday to Thursday:
OL,13,FSunshine and showers Tuesday and
OL,14,FWednesday with a risk of hail and
OL,15,Fthunder. A fine start likely on
OL,16,FThursday, then rain arriving later.
OL,17,FBreezy at times and rather cool
OL,18,Foverall.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
